public class LSPMetaAttributeSet
extends LSPObject

This helper object fits inside the LSPMetaAttributes object, which, as per STARTS 1.0, stores all meta-attributes for a specific source. This object has been hardcoded with the mbasic1 attributes. Its attributes are separate from LSPMetaAttributes, following the way the STARTS protocol separates them - but really all this class is is a collection of even more attributes.

There are getter methods for reading all the attributes after instantiation, but they are rarely used; the framework reads this object using the toXML() method.

LSPMetaAttributeSet

public LSPMetaAttributeSet(java.lang.String sourceLanguage,
                           java.lang.String sourceName,
                           java.lang.String class_t,
                           java.lang.String linkage,
                           java.lang.String contentSummaryLinkage,
                           java.lang.String dateChanged,
                           java.lang.String dateExpires,
                           java.lang.String abstrct,
                           java.lang.String accessConstants,
                           java.lang.String contact)
See the STARTS 1.0 specification for more details of these parameters Note that linkage and contentSummaryLinkage must not be null, or an error will result. Any of the others can be.

Parameters:
sourceLanguage - the (human) language of the underlying subcollection
sourceName - the name of the subcollection. This is obtainable via the getName() method of BackEndLSP
class_t - the class the this collection belongs to
linkage - the "linkage" of the underlying collection - how to reach it directly without SDARTS (usually via a web server, etc.)
contentSummaryLinkage - where to find the content summary. This is a good way to make an XML version of LSPContentSummary available without using SDARTS, since typically content summaries are too big for SDLIP to deliver at the present time.
dateChanged - the last time the collection changed
dateExpires - when the collection information expires
abstrct - an abstract of the collection's contents. See if you can guess why the variable can't be called "abstract."
accessConstants - the access constants for the collection
contact - who to talk to about the subcollection
